{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_37","type":"agent_message","text":"The schema confirms there’s no richer resource-origin selector than `glob` or `bundle`, which explains why this is tricky with multiple root-level `reference.conf` files. I’m now checking whether this repo’s expected fix pattern is to use test-only metadata for these duplicate config resources instead of forcing them through the library metadata file."}}
